class Solution {
    public long minimumSteps(String s) {
        long swaps = 0;
        int zeros = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == '0') {
                zeros++;
            } else {
                swaps += zeros;
            }
        }
        return swaps;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Count how many '0's are to the left of each '1'; each such '0' must be swapped past that '1' to move all '1's to the right. The running count of zeros gives the exact number of swaps needed for each '1' encountered, summing these yields the minimal total swaps.

